If you give $100, you ll have $120 worth of credits to use at Mamaleh s over the year About Mamaleh s Delicatessen Mamaleh s Delicatessen opened in Cambridge in with the goal of bringing Jewish cuisine of decades past into the Boston Since opening, they’ve received much acclaim, including Bon Appetit Magazine s best new restaurants in the country, Boston Magazine s Best Deli, and become a beloved part of the Boston Thanks to their tremendously loyal staff and customers, Mamaleh’s is still fighting through the Covid era, and they plan to be a Boston area staple for years to Learn More What you re funding While was challenging to say the least, Mamaleh’s was resilient and turned the pandemic into an opportunity to try new Now, Mamaleh’s is taking these learnings and channeling them into opening its second location in Your contribution will allow Mamaleh’s to support their current staff, grow their team, and expand their positive impact beyond the Cambridge Contribute FAQ s I don t live in Massachusetts, can I still contribute to the campaign? Yes! Anyone in the US can contribute to the You ll be able to use your credits toward nationwide shipping When will I receive my credits? If the campaign goal is met, we ll email you a code for your first credits one month after the campaign You ll get more credits every month for one If the campaign goals aren t met, we ll return any amount contributed to the card you used to How do I use my credits? Simply enter the code you receive by email when checking out at Mamaleh s online or You ll be able to use your credits at Mamaleh s Cambridge and Brookline Your credits will expire days after you receive We want you to enjoy more of the bagels, lox and pastrami we ve all come to love from Mamaleh s. Learn More About Us We re a group of Cornell University students and alumni focused on addressing the issues surrounding emergency department With limited personnel and space, patients wait for several hours unmonitored in waiting rooms before receiving care, if at Unfortunately, ED overcrowding can often lead to increased walkouts, progression of illness, and VIEW MORE The Problem Over % of EDs experience overcrowding and % of the physicians we reached out to (n=115) are concerned of ED overcrowding and its Our Solution We are creating a device, VitalMask, that will provide continous monitoring for patients in waiting rooms and alert medical personnel of any Hardware Our device fits under a traditional surgical mask and is equipped with sensors that measure heart rate, SpO2 levels, temperature, and respiratory Software Our desktop application can connect to multiple devices through The application displays all recorded vitals and allows for custom thresholds alarm VitalMask turns any mask into a continuous monitoring system Use our software to simultaneously connect with multiple VitalMasks Buy Now VitalMask × VitalMask is still under product development at this Sign up to be on the waitlist and we ll reach out once our device is on the market! Advocacy | ASP Skip to Main Content Physician Led Care Home About Advocacy Media Membership Members Events Groups Blog Contact More Use tab to navigate through the menu Log In Our Advocacy American Society of Physicians is committed to ending the physician shortage and proposing and implementing sustainable solutions that would provide quality care to patients by qualified healthcare ​ The following statements summarize our advocacy efforts and our public positions on policies that affect healthcare in the United ​ Read our statements here: THE PROBLEM: Not Enough Residency Positions Each year, ~10,000 medical graduates are unable to obtain a residency In the process of becoming an MD, DO, or MBBS, a medical graduate accrues thousands of hours of clinical practice, but is unable to obtain a license to practice unless accepted into a residency Upon successful completion of medical school, medical graduates must pass several examinations and pay thousands of dollars into a system that does not guarantee them a training position - the only way to be licensed in the United There are several bills in the House and Senate that would increase the number of residency positions in high need areas and primary care but progress has been There are a few states that have adopted the Assistant Associate Physician In Missouri, it has been largely successful in increasing access to care in rural and underserved It also provides opportunities for medical graduates to be licensed to practice in primary care under the supervision of a physician who has full practice Get in Touch Email us for more information Box number: AVE S Seattle, WA (503) Submit Thanks for submitting! DeliverHealth Solutions Formed to Simplify Hospitals’ Challenges SOLUTIONS Provider Support » Advisory & Consulting » Clinical Documentation » Service Desk Patient Support » Advisory & Consulting » Patient Portal Workflow » Advisory & Consulting » eSOne Platform » Services EHR Performance » Advisory & Consulting » Activation & Adoption » Services » Managed Services ABOUT US Leadership Join Our Team NEWS CONTACT WE’RE HIRING Select Page PRESS RELEASE DeliverHealth Solutions Formed to Simplify Hospitals’ EHR, Documentation and Revenue Cycle Challenges New company brings leadership continuity, healthcare technology expertise, and thousands of HIM and EHR professionals ready to serve BURLINGTON, , , — DeliverHealth Solutions LLC (DeliverHealth), a new healthcare IT and revenue cycle services company, today announced its establishment as a proven, knowledgeable partner for hospitals and health DeliverHealth was formed by Assured Healthcare Partners (AHP) in partnership with Aeries Technology Group (Aeries) from the of the health information management (HIM), transcription and electronic health record (EHR) services businesses of Nuance Communications, (Nuance). The HIM business of DeliverHealth will include both Nuance Transcription Services (NTS) and the eScription technology The transaction is expected to be completed in early and Nuance will be a minority shareholder of “Together, we’re all facing a ‘new now’ in healthcare, one that requires talented people and a sharp focus to prioritize patients over technology,” said Michael Clark, CEO of DeliverHealth upon the closing of the “Clinical documentation, revenue cycle and EHR complexity challenges have never been more prevalent or pervasive, negatively impacting physician satisfaction and an organization’s bottom DeliverHealth will simplify these challenges through decades of HIM knowledge, proven EHR expertise, and a consistent leadership and service We are grateful for the support provided by AHP, Aeries and Nuance to create what will be a winning formula for our customers and our dedicated team of more than 2,000 ” As an independent company in today’s crowded healthcare IT and revenue cycle marketplace, DeliverHealth will differentiate its offerings with continuity of the senior leadership team, access to exceptional healthcare technology and a proven service The company will build on HIM, transcription, technology and EHR services already in place while expanding into intelligent, revenue cycle automation and clinical documentation improvement services within the EHR’s workflow in Through a proven team of dedicated healthcare professionals, DeliverHealth will achieve its mission to: Remove productivity barriers in service delivery Relieve physician documentation burdens Redesign the customer service experience Simplify how healthcare organizations connect with technology “Our vision is to be a consistent, knowledgeable partner for hospitals and health systems by delivering a simpler documentation, revenue cycle and EHR experience,” said “Great accomplishments will come from DeliverHealth’s teamwork and mutual dedication to our customers’ ” To discover how DeliverHealth will simplify healthcare complexities and liberate providers to focus on caring for their patients, visit . Move from BigCommerce V2 to V3 Feature Tips • September 9, How to Successfully Move from BigCommerce V2 to V3 As a merchant on BigCommerce, you should be familiar with their focus to stop supporting the V2 Products API in lieu of support for the more robust V3 All new storefronts going forward will be required to be on V3 and over time support for V2 will While the upgrade can be done with the click of a button – the outcome depends largely on how your store is Significant changes were made to the way product options, option sets, variants, and SKUs work under BigCommerce recommends vetting the effects of the upgrade to make sure no adverse effects With BigCommerce’s recent successful IPO, they will continue their focus to further enhance the API and thus continuing the need for seamless Having a test environment that is a mirror of your live storefront where you could perform the upgrade without worry of it breaking your live store is a That ability previously did not exist, but now a new BigCommerce app fills that StoreReflect is a new , marketplace application that enables BigCommerce merchants to synchronize data between Now you can have a clone of your production catalog in a safe environment to vet your upgrade StoreReflect works with V2 and V3 It also offers additional features like data backup, content restoration, and catalog We built StoreReflect to ease the day to day operation of your The app allows merchants the ability to build catalog data in a staging environment, and only push it to production when it is fully This is the same theory that is at play where a BigCommerce product upgrade needs to be vetted in a environment as Now you can be sure that the data in your test environment is a direct mirror of production, prior to the The result is a secure upgrade path, and a good nights’ sleep knowing you will not break For more information on how to get started, contact our team today ! What can the rig team use to monitor the well for instability indicators? ​ CleanSight™ of course! No more reliance on intermittent visits to the shakers, mud loggers, or expensive LWD to detect if the hole is becoming Only CleanSight™ can pick this up 7. type of loss or a cause of loss that is specifically not covered by your homeowners insurance Your policy will have an exclusions section that will list losses that are specifically Expiration date is the date when your insurance policy Flood insurance protects against damage from rising or overflowing bodies of Your homeowners policy usually doesn’t cover flooding, but you can buy flood insurance Insured means the policyholder(s), those protected in the event of a Loss Assessment is coverage for shared losses when your condo or home is part of an Loss of Use is coverage that pays for additional living expenses, such as hotel costs and meals, if your insured residence becomes uninhabitable due to a covered loss and you temporarily This coverage is sometimes called additional living or temporary living Loss Payee is someone who has a financial interest in the property and can receive insurance payments in the event of a covered Loss payees can include the property owners and mortgage Medical Payment to Others is insurance that pays the cost of medical care to an injured guest in your Ordinance or Law Coverage is additional coverage for rebuilding or repairing your home to meet current laws or building Other Structures is the part of your homeowners insurance policy that covers buildings on your property other than your home, such as a detached garage or Personal Liability is coverage that financially protects you in the event of an accident, whether at your home or away from it, that results in bodily injury or property damage that you’re legally responsible Personal Property Coverage is for property in your home, such as furniture, clothing, and other items you own that are not Replacement cost coverage is coverage that pays the replacement

Getting to Grips with Shopify SEO Navigate back to the homepage Copied Getting to Grips with Shopify SEO Connor Whitman , August , · 7 min read Copied So you’ve built an amazing storefront and have a killer product that everybody wants to buy - or so you think - but you need to get people through the front door And to do that, you need to make sure that your customers can find your store Online shopping is the norm today because of that there is a lot of noise out there, and that means you’re competing with an number of brands for your customers’ time and Luckily, there’s plenty of things you can do to ensure you’re getting in front of as many motivated buyers as But before we dive into that, let’s address one extremely common question: Is Shopify even good for SEO? Categorically YES! Not only are you working on a great platform that gives you extremely granular control over every aspect of your online store - SEO included - you get the benefits of an CDN (content delivery network) powered by Fastly . You don’t need to be a tech expert and get into the details, what matters is this means that your store will load reliably, and quickly anywhere on the Site performance is a major technical SEO factor , so the fact that Shopify eliminates the time and cost overhead of site optimization and management means you get to spend your time focusing on running and growing your The short version is that not only is Shopify good for SEO, it makes it easy to So, what can you do without having to hire a pro to maximize your Shopify store’s SEO? I’ll split this into two categories: things specific to Shopify, and things relevant to web SEO in General SEO This is the stuff you need to be doing at the bare minimum for all your web It’s not hard, just tedious, so the sooner and more often you get it taken care of and set up, the easier your life will be! I’ll only touch on the major points of these, but for a really look at SEO go read my How To SEO Audit series of Keyword Research The first thing you absolutely must do is nail down your keyword You might think you know exactly what keywords to target, but this will let you figure out that out for sure and give you a better understanding of both your market and how they’re looking and searching for what you Keyword research is probably going to be the most time consuming portion of your Shopify SEO journey, but trust me - it will pay off dividends And remember - it’s automatically giving you a leg up on your competitors who don’t take the time to do this step right, or at all! First things first - most ‘first pass’ keywords are broad and don’t have Let’s take a step back and figure out: Who is it that you’re targeting? What problem do they have that you solve? Why are they trying to solve that issue? When searching for solutions to this issue, how do they do so? What questions are they asking? What specific words are they using? Why does that issue exist in the first place? How do you solve that issue for them? Going through the exercise of these questions puts you in a much better place to “get” your buyer’s behavior, intent, and search habits, letting you better form your keyword Not only that, it has the secondary benefits of informing both your content strategy and your lead capture system and sales funnels! From this point you can jump into determining search volumes, related keywords, expanding into keywords, recording the competition landscape - but above all else, ensure that while you’re going through that exercise you keep in mind your buyer’s intent, and how you are solving a problem for Review and Grow Your Content Marketing Content is king in the eyes of Google, and it’s your number one tool in winning the SEO game when you don’t yet have an established backlink This is your time to shine with content that directly addresses those buyer problems we were talking about Giving them content where they can be the hero of the story using your products to achieve success is one of the most tried and true and Also, realize that you often need to build up a relationship with prospective Consumers aren’t impulse purchasing as much as they used to, and for better or worse there’s a significantly longer sales cycle for consumer goods than we’ve seen in the past as reviews and ratings are only a few searches So leverage your content to start establishing a relationship where you provide value before any money has even exchanged No one likes the pushy salesman, don’t let your content be that guy! And then remember: great content gets shared - and really great content that gets shared gets This is ultimately what we want to aim for make sure your blog and other content pieces are genuinely useful to your audience and not just a sales Technical Shopify SEO This is thankfully mostly hands off here because of Shopify’s Even so, there are a few and sanity checks you should First up is to review your site’s link If you have any old products that moved or were discontinued, you will

Thinking Articles Join us process guide This guide introduces the basics of impact thinking—a method of creating products that change the Top Six steps Defining a problem Setting a goal We create this guide for teams , for people who build their organizations not only to earn money, but also to make really meaningful things and significant changes in the Our goal is to make the creation of products available to every team on Our approach to impact thinking is a result of compiling and reimagining modern knowledge , approaches and tools for designing products and processes, ideas of social and environmental responsibility, and latest discoveries in management and Impact activities often go hand in hand with responsibility and Read our article about differences between them . The main task of impact activity is to change the system that the team is working Six steps of Changing the world sounds For many, as something These six steps will show you a system that you can follow to make changing the world your inspiring daily 1 Defining a problem What is going on? What we don t like? What are the root causes? What are the bad consequences? How do we want it to be? Who are involved and what are their visions and interests? 2 Setting a goal Where do we want to get? What is an optimal method and why? How do we know we have succeeded? When can we stop? What is the ultimate goal? 3 Designing an impact What process should we build to start Whose life will change and how will they feel it? How will we measure a progress towards? Who is interested in a change and would love to join? What can they bring to a process? How can we facilitate their participation? 4 Funding the changes Who and how will benefit from a shift? How can we measure it? How can we borrow a part of those benefits in future to make a change today? 5 Measuring and managing the process How big is the problem? Does it evolve? What are the critical values and conditions? What changes are irreversible? How rapid do we affect? Do we have enough resources? What and how will we measure to see desired changes? How do we know we have reliable data? 6 Communicating the aspirations and achievements Who is interested in knowing what we do? Why are they and what they wish to know? What is the best way to provide that information? How to get feedback from them? Defining a problem The more we know about the problem, the more accurate, effective and cheap the solution will Every specific problem is always a part of a bigger system and a longer And every problem is always a solution for someone else s another When we plan any change, the first part is to define a current Where we are and what we want to change? The most common mistake here is to start acting without enough understanding of the This often leads to the common failures: infinite fighting with the consequences, strengthening the problem instead of defeating it, creating a new problem or just moving one to a new place, facing an unexpected resistance from other To define a problem properly we should answer the following questions: What is going on, and why do we think it s a problem? Who is experiencing a problem and how? How many of them, and how can we define and describe that group? Do they recognize a problem (or who else recognized it) and how? How did they try to solve it? What are the root causes of a problem? What are the bad consequences? What causes the problem to reproduce and not be resolved? Who are involved and what are their perspectives and interests? How did the problem appear and when (this often means: who created it and why)? And do those reasons still exist? How big and severe is a problem? What numbers and estimates do we have? Five whys—the great method to find a root cause of a problem Click to read more or see the full article on Wikipedia Five whys (or 5 whys ) is an iterative interrogative technique used to explore the relationships underlying a particular [1] The primary goal of the technique is to determine the root cause of a defect or problem by repeating the question "Why?". Each answer forms the basis of the next The "five" in the name derives from an anecdotal observation on the number of iterations needed to resolve the Not all problems have a single root If one wishes to uncover multiple root causes, the method must be repeated asking a different sequence of questions each The method provides no hard and fast rules about what lines of questions to explore, or how long to continue the search for additional root Thus, even when the method is closely followed, the outcome still depends upon the knowledge and persistence of the people What is a good way to define a problem? Picture Orville about ready to take flight: was he concerned about the risk or excited about the possibilities? Was Wilbur concerned for his brother’s health or focused on learning from this next attempt at achieving their goal? Most business owners we know can relate to these emotions and challenges, and to us, this story is a metaphor for the many business owners we They’re motivated, focused and passionate about their They are inspired by what may be and are looking for ways to take that next Ten:34 Partners may be a key to helping your business take that next The Wright Brothers found the key to flight by adding the mechanic, Charlie Taylor, to the He had the skillset to build an engine that was light enough and powerful enough to allow flight to Might Ten:34 be your Charlie Taylor — supplementing your business acumen with our skillset to get to that next point in accomplishing your objectives? There will always be similarities and differences in The key is whether we’re getting to the answers that you and Ten:34 feel good about when we work If so, that’s a good basis for a strong What’s important to you in selecting a partner? ERC FAQ’s | Reindeer Consultants [email protected] Home ERC FAQ’s Contact Us Home ERC FAQ’s Contact Us [email protected] [email protected] Home ERC FAQ’s Contact Us Don t Disqualify Yourself from The Employee Retention Congress recently updated the Employee Retention Credit (ERC), which is the most lucrative tax break available to business Unfortunately many business owners are disqualifying themselves based on outdated Many companies that… • Did not see a drop in revenue • Were deemed an essential business • Claimed PPP Are still qualifying for the Employee Retention The key to qualifying is not just revenue–if you had to alter your in any way due to the pandemic, you are well positioned to receive federal funding to invest back into your Explore More What is the Employee Retention Credit? The Employee Retention Credit (“ERC”) continues to provide a wide variety of employers with lucrative refundable payroll tax credits for qualified wages paid to employees in and Businesses can still apply for the ERC by filing an amended Form (Quarterly Federal Payroll Tax Return) for the quarters during which the company was an Eligible The ERC is a refundable credit that businesses can claim on qualified wages, including certain health insurance costs, paid to CARES Act – For employers who qualify, including borrowers who took a loan under the initial PPP, the credit can be claimed against percent of qualified wages paid, up to $10,000 per employee annually for wages paid between March and , Consolidated Appropriations Act – Employers who qualify, including PPP recipients, can claim a credit against % of qualified wages Additionally, the amount of wages that qualifies for the credit is now $10,000 per employee per quarter for the first two quarters of Can I get both the ERC and PPP Loan? While an employer may not include wages funded by a PPP loan in the ERC calculation, PPP funds only apply to eight to ten weeks of wage The ERC eligibility periods are PPP loans can also fund For ERC PPP funding may be allocated to wages that would not generate any ERC (e.g., to owners of the company or to wages in excess of $10,000 in one of the four ERC periods). Autism & Applied Behavior Analysis What is Applied Behavior Analysis?: To understand applied behavior analysis or ABA, we must first understand behavior Behavior analysis or the science of behavior is the study of principles of learning and Behavior analysis is built on the philosophy that the environment influences behavior meaning the environment, or what’s happening around us, directly impacts what we Behavior analysis is often divided into two primary areas, the experimental analysis of behavior and applied behavior The experimental analysis of behavior focuses on studying and evaluating the fundamental and basic principles of Basically, they study what changes behavior and how different things influence What we learn in this area of the science is then used to guide behavioral change procedures in the real world in applied behavior Applied behavior analysis (ABA) uses the principles from the science of behavior to systematically change behaviors that are meaningful to those in the individual’s The goal of ABA is to improve the quality of life for our clients and those around ABA targets behavior in settings such as in the home, school, clinics, industry, and community and often targets socially important behaviors such as problematic behaviors and At Arise Autism Center, we provide services that are in line with the dimensions of ABA by using systematic observation, data We conduct thorough behavioral assessments, analyze daily data to allow for continuous revisions of the treatment plan, and conduct ongoing caregiver and staff training to ensure our services generalize to all areas of the individual’s Although ABA is one of the most common treatments for autism, it should be noted that ABA is more than a treatment for ABA has been shown to be effective in a variety of settings targeting a large range of Behavior analysts are qualified to work in areas such as improving organizational behavior and functioning, increasing workplace safety, improving athletic performance and addressing developmental and skill deficits, education, and behavior Autism: Autism spectrum disorder (ASD) is a group of developmental disabilities that are characterized by significant deficits in the areas of social interaction, communication, and or behavior A diagnosis of ASD includes those with conditions that used to be diagnosed separately such as: autistic disorder, pervasive developmental disorder not otherwise specified (PDD-NOS), and Asperger’s Autism Facts: The Centers for Diseas

About — Huemon 0 Skip to Content Open Menu Close Menu Open Menu Close Menu Our Story Early in life my parents taught me the effectiveness of just asking questions in order to connect with I’ve applied this whenever meeting new people, and it’s helped me build strong friendships rooted in openness and This approach has also helped me connect with others who come from very different backgrounds to Bonding over things like a treasured childhood memory or a moment when they felt like an outsider goes a long way in building empathy and combating unconscious I wanted to package all of this up into Huemon as a tool that helps people communicate in more intimate The true potential of Huemon really clicked for me when I started to think more broadly about how it could help people battling personal There are so many of us who are afraid to open up because we think we are alone in our experiences, and that others can’t relate or would judge We avoid seeking out assistance because we believe there is a stigma to needing My goal is for Huemon to provide a , space for people to unpack their personal experiences and feel validated in the fact that they share in the common human Tamara Dottin, Founder Blog About Us C
